; ============================================================
; Notes on the Schema/* primitives
;
; This file references several "Schema/*" primitives:
;   - Schema/verify_type_tag (Bytes, TypeTag) → Bool (traps)
;   - Schema/bytes_in_range  (Bytes, Nat, Nat) → Bytes
;   - Schema/nat_at          (Bytes, Nat) → Nat
;   - Schema/mul             (Nat, Nat) → Nat
;   - Schema/tail_hash       (Bytes) → Hash
;   - Schema/tail_minus_8_nat(Bytes) → Nat
;   - Schema/vec_from_offset (Bytes, Nat) → Vec
;
; These are pure structural helpers over byte vectors. They are
; smaller than the projections themselves (each is 3-5
; instructions of IL: SUB or LOAD + structural cast). They
; will be encoded in a sibling file in a subsequent v0.2.0
; batch as kernel/forms/helpers/schema-primitives.form. Until
; then, the projections have one pending leaf at the inner
; CALL — but the indirection is now complete at the schema
; layer, and the schema layer's pending leaves are at a known,
; finite, well-specified set of primitives.
; ============================================================
